==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Calippic
<hw>Ca*lip"pic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
<etsep>Calippus</etsep>, an Athenian astronomer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Calippic period</b></col>, <cd>a period of seventy-six
years, proposed by Calippus, as an improvement on the Metonic cycle,
since the 6940 days of the Metonic cycle exceeded 19 years by about a
quarter of a day, and exceeded 235 lunations by something
more.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calisaya bark</ent>⟦br⟧
